{"questionId":"28012","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>for 2<sup>nd</sup> particle,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">i</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">j</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>consider the gradient of either&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; and&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>12</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>vectors are parallel therefore one is a multiple of the other,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mi>l</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">v</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>l</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>16</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to solve&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>30</mn><mo> </mo><mfenced><mtext>s</mtext></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>30135</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"28012","referenceCode":"22N.2.AHL.TZ0.7d.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title"